Diagnosis. This new species is similar to
Bioramix ( Leipopleura ) rugelytra
sp. nov. , but can be distinguished from the latter by the following characters (based on male): (1) pronotum widest nearly at middle, surface with fine punctures on disc, denser and coarser at sides (at base, coarse on disc, dense at sides in
B. rugelytra
); (2) elytra with traces of longitudinal carinae (without in
B. rugelytra
); (3) metatibiae weakly curved (straight in
B. rugelytra
); (4) distal part of parameres strongly curved dorsally in lateral view (more weakly in
B. rugelytra
).
